WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.370 --> 00:00:03.700
Lobster is a delicacy and live, fresh lobster
is available in the western world.

00:00:03.700 --> 00:00:05.770
It looks like large tiger prawns available
in the Asian countries.

00:00:05.770 --> 00:00:21.650
And prawns being a sought after food in the
Bengali cuisine, we wanted to cook the lobster

00:00:21.650 --> 00:00:22.650
curry.

00:00:22.650 --> 00:00:23.940
For this recipe, we need,

00:00:23.940 --> 00:00:27.880
2 large lobsters cut into halves and cleaned
with shell on.

00:00:27.880 --> 00:00:31.600
We bought live lobsters for this recipe.

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:35.280
1 tbsp turmeric powder
salt to test

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:39.370
4 tbsp mustard oil
1 dry red chili

00:00:39.370 --> 00:00:43.179
1 bay leaf
1 1/2 cup chopped onion

00:00:43.179 --> 00:00:48.039
1 1/2 tbsp chopped garlic
1 1/2 tbsp chopped ginger

00:00:48.039 --> 00:00:54.129
1 tsp roasted cumin powder
1/4 tsp chili powder (or to taste)

00:00:54.129 --> 00:00:57.679
2 cups chopped tomato
1 can cocoanut milk

00:00:57.679 --> 00:01:02.059
1/2 tsp Bengali garam masala
2 sliced green chilies

00:01:02.059 --> 00:01:08.340
The recipe consists of three steps:
Marinate the cleaned lobster with turmeric

00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:11.730
and salt
Sautee the onion with spices

00:01:11.730 --> 00:01:18.500
Then mix the spices with the coconut milk,
the lobster and cook to completion

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:21.200
Place cleaned and washed lobster halves on
a plate

00:01:21.200 --> 00:01:31.800
Add 1 tbsp turmeric powder
Add 1 tsp salt

00:01:31.800 --> 00:01:41.700
Marinate
You can see that the lobster is still alive.

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:50.310
set aside
heat a pan or wok to medium

00:01:50.310 --> 00:02:12.090
add about 2 tbsp mustard oil
let oil warm up

00:02:12.090 --> 00:02:26.930
add the marinated lobster halves into the
oil

00:02:26.930 --> 00:02:45.780
fry both sides till it picks up golden red
color

00:02:45.780 --> 00:03:14.239
then remove from the heat and set aside
add 2 tbsp oil to the same wok and heat it

00:03:14.239 --> 00:03:18.959
up
add the dry red chili, broken to half

00:03:18.959 --> 00:03:51.150
add 1 bay leaf broken in half
add the chopped onion

00:03:51.150 --> 00:03:58.310
fry till onion softens and becomes translucent
add chopped garlic

00:03:58.310 --> 00:04:13.790
add chopped ginger
stir for 2-3 minutes

00:04:13.790 --> 00:04:21.750
add roasted cumin powder
add the chili powder

00:04:21.750 --> 00:04:46.270
add the chopped tomato
add about a tsp salt

00:04:46.270 --> 00:04:53.319
stir till tomatoes mix together with spices
and becomes thick paste

00:04:53.319 --> 00:05:11.460
add 1 small can of cocoanut milk
stir for a minute

00:05:11.460 --> 00:05:33.120
wash the milk can with water and add into
the mix

00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:52.389
add the fried lobster halves
stir

00:05:52.389 --> 00:06:01.120
cover
let the mixture come to boil

00:06:01.120 --> 00:06:15.300
remove the cover
you can adjust the consistency by adding water,

00:06:15.300 --> 00:06:25.720
if needed
test for salt and add if needed

00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:39.699
if you add water, then bring it to boil again
add Bengali garam masala

00:06:39.699 --> 00:06:49.949
mix
turn off the heat

00:06:49.949 --> 00:06:51.550
garnish with 2 sliced green chilies

00:06:51.550 --> 00:06:55.060
This completes the lobster curry.

00:06:55.060 --> 00:06:58.770
Takes about 40-45 minutes
Serve the curry with hot steamed Basmati rice

00:06:58.770 --> 00:06:59.060
or chapatti.

